>def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Batteries/Data/Float/Basic.html#Float32.toRatParts'\"><span class=\"name\">Float32</span>.<span class=\"name\">toRatParts'</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">f</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float.html#Float\">Float</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Option\">Option</a> (<a href=\"./Init/Data/Int/Basic.html#Int\">Int</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Prod\">×</a> <a href=\"./Init/Data/Int/Basic.html#Int\">Int</a>)</span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Returns `v, exp` integers such that `f = v * 2^exp`.\nLike `toRatParts`, but `e` is guaranteed to be minimal (`v` is always odd), unless `v = 0`.\n`v.abs` will be at most `2^24 - 1` because `Float` has 24 bits of precision.\nReturns `none` when `f` is not finite (i.e. `inf`, `-inf` or a `nan`). ","docLink":"./Batteries/Data/Float/Basic.html#Float32.toRatParts'","kind":"def","line":119,"name":"Float32.toRatParts'","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/batteries/blob/0a7a0cdc42f531e02361cb303b8cbf0e7d334f82/Batteries/Data/Float/Basic.lean#L119-L135"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Batteries/Data/Float/Basic.html#Float32.toRatParts\"><span class=\"name\">Float32</span>.<span class=\"name\">toRatParts</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">f</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32\">Float32</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Option\">Option</a> (<a href=\"./Init/Data/Int/Basic.html#Int\">Int</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Prod\">×</a> <a href=\"./Init/Data/Int/Basic.html#Int\">Int</a>)</span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Returns `v, exp` integers such that `f = v * 2^exp`.\n(`e` is not minimal, but `v.abs` will be at most `2^24 - 1`.)\nReturns `none` when `f` is not finite (i.e. `inf`, `-inf` or a `nan`). ","docLink":"./Batteries/Data/Float/Basic.html#Float32.toRatParts","kind":"def","line":105,"name":"Float32.toRatParts","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/batteries/blob/0a7a0cdc42f531e02361cb303b8cbf0e7d334f82/Batteries/Data/Float/Basic.lean#L105-L117"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Batteries/Data/Float/Basic.html#Float32.pi\"><span class=\"name\">Float32</span>.<span class=\"name\">pi</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32\">Float32</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The floating point value closest to the mathematical constant `π`.\n","docLink":"./Batteries/Data/Float/Basic.html#Float32.pi","kind":"def","line":100,"name":"Float32.pi","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/batteries/blob/0a7a0cdc42f531e02361cb303b8cbf0e7d334f82/Batteries/Data/Float/Basic.lean#L100-L103"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Batteries/Data/Float/Basic.html#Float32.nan\"><span class=\"name\">Float32</span>.<span class=\"name\">nan</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32\">Float32</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The floating point value \"not a number\", used to represent erroneous numerical computations\nsuch as `0 / 0`. Using `nan` in any float operation will return `nan`, and all comparisons\ninvolving `nan` return `false`, including in particular `nan == nan`.\n","docLink":"./Batteries/Data/Float/Basic.html#Float32.nan","kind":"def","line":93,"name":"Float32.nan","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/batteries/blob/0a7a0cdc42f531e02361cb303b8cbf0e7d334f82/Batteries/Data/Float/Basic.lean#L93-L98"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Batteries/Data/Float/Basic.html#Float32.inf\"><span class=\"name\">Float32</span>.<span class=\"name\">inf</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32\">Float32</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The floating point value \"positive infinity\", also used to represent numerical computations\nwhich produce finite values outside of the representable range of `Float32`.\n","docLink":"./Batteries/Data/Float/Basic.html#Float32.inf","kind":"def","line":87,"name":"Float32.inf","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/batteries/blob/0a7a0cdc42f531e02361cb303b8cbf0e7d334f82/Batteries/Data/Float/Basic.lean#L87-L91"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Batteries/Data/Float/Basic.html#Float.toStringFull\"><span class=\"name\">Float</span>.<span class=\"name\">toStringFull</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">f</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float.html#Float\">Float</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#String\">String</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Converts `f` to a string, including all decimal digits. ","docLink":"./Batteries/Data/Float/Basic.html#Float.toStringFull","kind":"def","line":64,"name":"Float.toStringFull","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/batteries/blob/0a7a0cdc42f531e02361cb303b8cbf0e7d334f82/Batteries/Data/Float/Basic.lean#L64-L81"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">partial def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Batteries/Data/Float/Basic.html#Float.toRatParts'.trailingZeros\"><span class=\"name\">Float</span>.<span class=\"name\">toRatParts'</span>.<span class=\"name\">trailingZeros</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">v</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#UInt64\">UInt64</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">c</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#UInt8\">UInt8</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#UInt8\">UInt8</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Calculates the number of trailing bits in a `UInt64`. Requires `v ≠ 0`. ","docLink":"./Batteries/Data/Float/Basic.html#Float.toRatParts'.trailingZeros","kind":"opaque","line":61,"name":"Float.toRatParts'.trailingZeros","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/batteries/blob/0a7a0cdc42f531e02361cb303b8cbf0e7d334f82/Batteries/Data/Float/Basic.lean#L61-L62"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Batteries/Data/Float/Basic.html#Float.toRatParts'\"><span class=\"name\">Float</span>.<span class=\"name\">toRatParts'</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">f</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float.html#Float\">Float</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Option\">Option</a> (<a href=\"./Init/Data/Int/Basic.html#Int\">Int</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Prod\">×</a> <a href=\"./Init/Data/Int/Basic.html#Int\">Int</a>)</span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Returns `v, exp` integers such that `f = v * 2^exp`.\nLike `toRatParts`, but `e` is guaranteed to be minimal (`v` is always odd), unless `v = 0`.\n`v.abs` will be at most `2^53 - 1` because `Float` has 53 bits of precision.\nReturns `none` when `f` is not finite (i.e. `inf`, `-inf` or a `nan`). ","docLink":"./Batteries/Data/Float/Basic.html#Float.toRatParts'","kind":"def","line":44,"name":"Float.toRatParts'","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/batteries/blob/0a7a0cdc42f531e02361cb303b8cbf0e7d334f82/Batteries/Data/Float/Basic.lean#L44-L62"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Batteries/Data/Float/Basic.html#Float.toRatParts\"><span class=\"name\">Float</span>.<span class=\"name\">toRatParts</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">f</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float.html#Float\">Float</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Option\">Option</a> (<a href=\"./Init/Data/Int/Basic.html#Int\">Int</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Prod\">×</a> <a href=\"./Init/Data/Int/Basic.html#Int\">Int</a>)</span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Returns `v, exp` integers such that `f = v * 2^exp`.\n(`e` is not minimal, but `v.abs` will be at most `2^53 - 1`.)\nReturns `none` when `f` is not finite (i.e. `inf`, `-inf` or a `nan`). ","docLink":"./Batteries/Data/Float/Basic.html#Float.toRatParts","kind":"def","line":30,"name":"Float.toRatParts","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/batteries/blob/0a7a0cdc42f531e02361cb303b8cbf0e7d334f82/Batteries/Data/Float/Basic.lean#L30-L42"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Batteries/Data/Float/Basic.html#Float.pi\"><span class=\"name\">Float</span>.<span class=\"name\">pi</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float.html#Float\">Float</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The floating point value closest to the mathematical constant `π`.\n","docLink":"./Batteries/Data/Float/Basic.html#Float.pi","kind":